class Solution:
    def lexicalOrder(self, n: int) -> List[int]:
        res = []
        cur = 1
        for _ in range(n):
            res.append(cur)
            if cur * 10 <= n:
                cur *= 10
            else:
                if cur >= n:
                    cur //= 10
                cur += 1
                while cur % 10 == 0:
                    cur //= 10
        return res
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Generates the sequence in lexicographical order by simulating a depth-first preorder traversal without recursion or extra storage. Starts at 1, always tries to append a zero (go deeper), otherwise increments and strips trailing zeros to backtrack correctly.

